ğŸ’¡ Tip: Use cd ~/Downloads to jump to your Downloads folder quickly.

ğŸ“‚ ls â€“ List Contents

ls              # List files
ls -l           # Long format
ls -lh          # Human-readable sizes
ls -a           # Show hidden files
ls -lhS         # Sort by size
ls -lt          # Sort by time modified

ğŸ’¡ Tip: Use ls -lah often to see everything in a directory including file sizes.
ğŸ“¤ File Operations

ğŸ“„ cp â€“ Copy Files and Directories

cp file1.txt file2.txt         # Copy file
cp -r folder1/ folder2/        # Copy directories recursively

ğŸ”€ mv â€“ Move or Rename Files

mv file.txt /backup/           # Move file
mv oldname.txt newname.txt     # Rename file

âš ï¸ cp copies. mv moves or renames. mv removes the original.

ğŸ› ï¸ Using tr â€“ Translate or Delete Characters

echo "HELLO WORLD" | tr 'A-Z' 'a-z'

Converts uppercase to lowercase.

echo "Hello  World" | tr -s ' '

-s: Squeeze repeated characters (e.g., multiple spaces to one).

echo "123abc" | tr -d '0-9'

-d: Delete characters in set.

